Micro Focus Careers


Our Careers
Diversity
Graduates and Careers
Benefits and Culture





Micro Focus understands the success of our work depends on the quality of the people we ask to do it. From the back-end office through to sales and support, if we are to thrive and survive in a fiercely-competitive marketplace, then we need the best-in-class staff for every area.
That is why we offer the packages of rewards and benefits needed to attract and retain the best industry talent. Then we put in place the structures that help our people flourish, develop and take our company forward.
Our company provides IT solutions for some of the world’s biggest organizations and industries. Our products touch many lives, from booking an airline ticket to using a banking app, Micro Focus solutions are working behind the scenes to enable success.
So whether you are helping to make, sell, or support our great software, or assist the people who do, you will be making an essential contribution to our work.
In return, we make your work rewarding and fulfilling. Because at Micro Focus, we make software and build careers.




"Taking our Customers into Tomorrow"
Micro Focus strives as an organization to reflect the globally diverse audience that our software serves. Diverse perspectives, ideas and cultural benefits are critical to the development of quality products and services.
Micro Focus fosters diversity through recruiting outreach programs, community based career fairs, university career centers and internships, and graduate student programs.



Talented software developers are the heart of our business at Micro Focus. The graduate programme is a great way to start your career with Micro Focus, and comes with a competitive starting package. You will be guided by a mentor who will support your progress as your career develops. You will also have the opportunity to work in different teams to explore various technical challenges, or you may choose to specialize in one area.   Our development teams include some of the industry’s most gifted and original minds, and we enjoy a great team spirit in a relaxed, yet professional goal-oriented atmosphere working on a very broad range of technologies.
Our current graduates voted via the JobCrowd (UK’s leading graduate job review website) and placed Micro Focus in the Top 10 IT and Telecommunication companies for IT graduates to work for, with nearly 5/5 stars.



Focused on Customer Success
Micro Focus has a culture of listening and learning, where colleagues work as one: supporting each other, holding each other accountable, and providing fast, flawless execution. Our number one mission is our customers’ successes.
We value a productive workplace where colleagues treat each other with respect, integrity, honesty, and openness.  The principles of the Micro Focus Professional Charter reinforce our actions on a daily basis:
Collaborate for success
As a team, we work together across functions and geographies in support of each opportunity. We focus on customer needs and success. We celebrate our successes.
Close the communications loop
Act upon requests and seek feedback to continually improve processes and customer satisfaction.
Respond promptly
Responding fast and flawlessly leads to superb customer satisfaction for internal and external customers.
Deliver on commitments
We build trust and respect with our customers through high quality and timely delivery.
Take responsibility & initiative
Colleagues are empowered to make a change within the organization.
Get involved, debate passionately, get on board
Be open, be involved, embrace change and be part of creating a successful organization.









