 Home ›Investor RelationsInvestor Relations

Welcome to the Micro Focus Investor Relations 
section. Here you will find the latest regulatory news and shareholder information from Micro Focus.

About Micro Focus
Micro Focus International is a global enterprise infrastructure software company that understands the technology needs and challenges of the world’s most demanding businesses.   With more than 35 years of experience and expertise, Micro Focus International helps organizations to bridge the old and the new.  As a result of our products and solutions, customers are better able to gain competitive advantage, adapt and innovate as a result of emerging IT trends, while also protecting corporate information.
The company has revenues of approximately $1.4 billion, more than 4,500 employees, more than 5,000 partners operating across more than 30 countries and a customer base well in excess of 20,000. Principal brands of Micro Focus International are: Attachmate, Borland, Micro Focus, NetIQ, Novell and SUSE.
Find out more about Micro Focus
