Micro Focus International plc Key Developments

Micro Focus International plc Announces Second Interim Dividend, Payable on August 25, 2017
Jul 12 17
The directors of Micro Focus International plc announced a second interim dividend of 58.33 cents per share against 49.74 cents per share a year ago. The dividend will be paid in Sterling equivalent to 45.22 pence per share, based on an exchange rate of £1 = $1.29 being the rate applicable on July 11, 2017, the date on which the board resolved to propose the dividend. The dividend will be paid on August 25, 2017 to shareholders on the register at August 4, 2017.


Micro Focus International plc Reports Preliminary Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Year Ended April 30, 2017
Jul 12 17
Micro Focus International plc reported preliminary unaudited consolidated earnings results for the year ended April 30, 2017. For the year, the company reported revenue of $1,380,702,000 against $1,245,049,000 last year. Operating profit was $293,443,000 against $294,934,000 last year. Profit before tax was $196,344,000 against $195,396,000 last year. Profit attributable to equity shareholders of the parent was $157,906,000 or 66.51 cents per diluted share against $162,894,000 or 71.61 cents per diluted share last year. Net cash generated from operating activities was $452,379,000 against $283,219,000 last year. Payments for intangible assets were $31,438,000 against $34,488,000 last year. Purchase of property, plant and equipment was $11,727,000 against $10,281,000 last year. Adjusted operating profit was $638.1 million against $616.5 million last year. Adjusted EBITDA was $651.1 million against $629.9 million last year. Underlying Adjusted EBITDA in the year increased by $25.6 million to $640.9 million. Adjusted profit before tax was $541.0 million compared to $516.8 million a year ago. Adjusted profit after tax was $417.0 million against $333.8 million a year ago. Adjusted diluted earnings per share increased by 19.7% to 175.65 cents. Net debt at 30 April 2017 was $1,410.6 million.


Micro Focus International Mulls Acquisitions
Jul 12 17
The board of Micro Focus International plc (LSE:MCRO) is confident that medium-term low single digit revenue growth, industry leading margins and strong cash conversion will ensure that Micro Focus can deliver on that strategy. These returns can be further enhanced by the appropriate deployment of capital in value enhancing acquisitions.


